<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/b8e30f4cf75e014a3b0239e5212a264f.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 7 and A = 55 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>4.9</li><li>8.5</li><li>35.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({55}\right)}}}=\frac{{7}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{7}}{{\tan{{\left({55}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{4.901452767468}\approx{4.9}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={7}^{{2}}+{4.901452767468}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={49}+{24.024239231719}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={73.024239231719}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{73.024239231719}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.5454221213302}\approx{8.5}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{55}^{\circ}\approx{35}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

